The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 April is 41,774 (4,835.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 April, there were 135 new confirmed cases (15.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 April, there were 149 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 9% (14 fewer cases).
